import TNLean.MPS.FundamentalTheorem.PaperBNT.DominantMatch

/-!
# Phase B-О± and B-ОІ (paper-faithful) strong existential and bijective matching

This module is **Phase B-О± and Phase B-ОІ** of the CPSV16/CPSV21
fundamental-theorem clean-slate plan (issue #1725).  The downstream
Phase B-Оі Corollary substitution argument
(`coeff_identity_via_global_gauge`, CPSV16 В§II.C lines 1187-1188) lives
in the companion module `PaperBNT/CoeffIdentity.lean` (file split in
PR #1729 to respect the 1000-line module limit).

The paper-faithful strong existential
matching theorem states the CPSV16 В§II.C lines 1182вЂ“1186 *Step 1*
conclusion directly on the original (un-dropped) pair `(P, Q)` of
BNT canonical forms, iterated over each sector `k` of `Q` that carries
a unit-modulus copy.

## Paper anchor

CPSV16 (arXiv:1606.00608) В§II.C lines 1182вЂ“1186, the *entire* "Step 1"
of the proof of Theorem `II_cor2` (verbatim):

> "Let us first consider $B_k$ for some given $k$.  It is not possible
> that $\langle V^{(N)}(B_k)|V^{(N)}(A_j)\rangle \to 0$ as $N\to\infty$
> for all $j$, since otherwise the MPV generated by $A$ and $B$ could
> not be proportional for all $N$ (Lemma `Lem1`).  Thus, according to
> Corollary `eqV`, there must exist one $j_k$ such that
> $|V^{(N)}(B_k)\rangle = e^{i\phi_k N} |V^{(N)}(A_{j_k})\rangle$.
> According to Lemma `equalMPS` we have $B_k = e^{i\phi_k} X_k A_{j_k} X_k^{-1}$."

The paper's "given $k$" is *iterated externally* over each unit-block
sector of `Q` (those with at least one unit-modulus weight, per the
CPSV16 В§II.A line-246 normalization which is recorded **globally** вЂ”
not per-block вЂ” in `IsBNTCanonicalForm.weight_unit_exists`).  Non-unit
blocks contribute coefficients that decay exponentially and so do not
constrain the matching; the paper restricts attention to the
"physical" (unit-modulus carrying) blocks.

## Scope (Phase B-О±)

The result is a **single `в€Ђ k, в€ѓ j` existential statement** on the
original pair, with the paper's "given $k$" hypothesis explicitly
encoded as the unit-modulus existential.  There is **no recursion**,
no `dropSector` usage, and no combined-LI obligation on a partial
union: the entire proof routes through the existing
`exists_block_match_of_sameMPV` lemma (which itself routes
through the full-family combined LI `combined_family_eventually_li`,
`PaperBNT/Api.lean`).

The downstream Phase B-ОІ (bijective matching) will apply this theorem
twice вЂ” once with `(P, Q)` and once with `(Q, P)` вЂ” to derive
`P.basisCount = Q.basisCount` on the unit-block subset and the per-pair
bijection / gauge data.

## Proof strategy (route B of the audit memo)

Given a sector `k` of `Q` with a unit-modulus weight, apply the
existing `exists_block_match_of_sameMPV` (`PaperBNT/DominantMatch`,
post-Phase-A rename in PR #1726) **with `P` and `Q` swapped**:

* feed `hQ`, `hP` (in that order);
* supply `hP_pos : 0 < P.basisCount` from `hP.weight_unit_exists`
  (which exists globally on `P`);
* supply the unit-modulus witness on `Q`'s `k` (the hypothesis of this
  theorem); and
* supply `SameMPVв‚‚ Q.toTensor P.toTensor` via the trivial symmetric
  flip of `hEqual` (pointwise `.symm`).

The result is a `jв‚Ђ : Fin P.basisCount` with `Q.basisDim k = P.basisDim jв‚Ђ`,
a gauge-phase equivalence in the `Q в†’ P` cast direction, and a
non-decaying overlap in the `(Q.basis k, P.basis jв‚Ђ)` order.  Two
local helpers (`gaugePhaseEquiv_swap_cast` and
`tendsto_mpvOverlap_zero_swap`) flip those into the paper-stated
`(P, Q)`-ordered conclusion.

All proofs in this file are closed constructively.
-/

open scoped Matrix BigOperators
open Filter Topology

namespace MPSTensor

variable {d : в„•}

/-! ### Local helpers: symmetry of `GaugePhaseEquiv` across a bond-dim cast -/

/-- Symmetry of `GaugePhaseEquiv` at a fixed bond dimension.

`GaugePhaseEquiv A B` says there exist a gauge `X в€€ GL` and a nonzero
scalar `О¶` such that `B i = О¶ вЂў (X * A i * XвЃ»В№)` for every physical
index `i`.  Conjugating by `XвЃ»В№` and scaling by `О¶вЃ»В№` gives the
reversed identity `A i = О¶вЃ»В№ вЂў (XвЃ»В№ * B i * X)`, i.e.
`GaugePhaseEquiv B A`. -/
private theorem gaugePhaseEquiv_symm_same_dim {d D : в„•} {A B : MPSTensor d D}
    (h : GaugePhaseEquiv A B) : GaugePhaseEquiv B A := by
  classical
  obtain вџЁX, О¶, hО¶, hrelвџ© := h
  refine вџЁXвЃ»В№, О¶вЃ»В№, inv_ne_zero hО¶, ?_вџ©
  intro i
  -- From `B i = О¶ вЂў (X * A i * XвЃ»В№)` derive `A i = О¶вЃ»В№ вЂў (XвЃ»В№ * B i * X)`.
  have hBi := hrel i
  -- Abbreviations for the matrix coercions.
  set XM : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) в„‚ := (X : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) в„‚)
  set XinvM : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) в„‚ :=
    ((XвЃ»В№ : GL (Fin D) в„‚) : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) в„‚)
  have hXX : XinvM * XM = (1 : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) в„‚) := by
    have hU : (XвЃ»В№ * X : GL (Fin D) в„‚) = 1 := by simp
    have hUval :
        ((XвЃ»В№ * X : GL (Fin D) в„‚) : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) в„‚)
          = ((1 : GL (Fin D) в„‚) : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) в„‚) :=
      congrArg Units.val hU
    simp only [Units.val_mul, Units.val_one] at hUval
    exact hUval
  have hXX' : XM * XinvM = (1 : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) в„‚) := by
    have hU : (X * XвЃ»В№ : GL (Fin D) в„‚) = 1 := by simp
    have hUval :
        ((X * XвЃ»В№ : GL (Fin D) в„‚) : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) в„‚)
          = ((1 : GL (Fin D) в„‚) : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) в„‚) :=
      congrArg Units.val hU
    simp only [Units.val_mul, Units.val_one] at hUval
    exact hUval
  -- Inverse-of-inverse: `(XвЃ»В№)вЃ»В№ = X` for units.
  have hInvInv : ((XвЃ»В№)вЃ»В№ : GL (Fin D) в„‚) = X := inv_inv X
  -- The desired identity: `A i = О¶вЃ»В№ вЂў (XвЃ»В№ * B i * X)`.
  -- Multiply `hBi : B i = О¶ вЂў (X * A i * XвЃ»В№)` on the left by `XвЃ»В№` and on
  -- the right by `X`:
  --   XвЃ»В№ * B i * X = О¶ вЂў (XвЃ»В№ * X * A i * XвЃ»В№ * X) = О¶ вЂў (1 * A i * 1) = О¶ вЂў A i.
  have hSandwich :
      XinvM * B i * XM = О¶ вЂў A i := by
    calc
      XinvM * B i * XM
          = XinvM * (О¶ вЂў (XM * A i * XinvM)) * XM := by rw [hBi]
      _ = О¶ вЂў (XinvM * (XM * A i * XinvM) * XM) := by
            simp
      _ = О¶ вЂў ((XinvM * XM) * A i * (XinvM * XM)) := by
            simp [Matrix.mul_assoc]
      _ = О¶ вЂў A i := by rw [hXX]; simp
  -- Now divide by `О¶`.
  have hAi : A i = О¶вЃ»В№ вЂў (XinvM * B i * XM) := by
    have := congrArg (fun M => (О¶вЃ»В№ : в„‚) вЂў M) hSandwich
    simp only [smul_smul, inv_mul_cancelв‚Ђ hО¶, one_smul] at this
    exact this.symm
  -- Repackage with the inverse of `XвЃ»В№` being `X`.
  -- The goal expects `((XвЃ»В№)вЃ»В№ : GL).val = X.val`.
  change A i = О¶вЃ»В№ вЂў (XinvM * B i *
    (((XвЃ»В№)вЃ»В№ : GL (Fin D) в„‚) : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) в„‚))
  simpa [hInvInv, XM, XinvM] using hAi

/-- Symmetry of `GaugePhaseEquiv` across a bond-dim cast: if the cast
maps the *right-hand* tensor into the *left-hand* space, then we may
flip both the cast direction and the equivalence direction.

The two forms are mathematically the same statement (after eliminating
the cast by `subst`), but the cast routing differs at the term level,
so we record this as an explicit helper used inside
`forall_k_exists_j_nondecaying_overlap_of_sameMPV`. -/
private theorem gaugePhaseEquiv_swap_cast {d Dв‚Ѓ Dв‚‚ : в„•}
    (h : Dв‚Ѓ = Dв‚‚) {A : MPSTensor d Dв‚Ѓ} {B : MPSTensor d Dв‚‚}
    (hGP : GaugePhaseEquiv (cast (congr_arg (MPSTensor d) h.symm) B) A) :
    GaugePhaseEquiv (cast (congr_arg (MPSTensor d) h) A) B := by
  subst h
  -- After `subst`, both casts reduce to identity.
  simpa using gaugePhaseEquiv_symm_same_dim (by simpa using hGP)

/-! ### Phase B-О± main theorem: paper-faithful full-basis matching -/

/-- **CPSV16 В§II.C lines 1182вЂ“1186 Step 1 (full-basis form).**

For every sector `k` of `Q`, there exists a sector `j` of `P` of equal
bond dimension, gauge-phase equivalent to `Q.basis k` after the dimension
cast, and with non-decaying cross-overlap.

The proof iterates `exists_block_match_of_sameMPV` over every `Q`-sector
with `(P, Q)` swapped, so it consumes the per-block unit-modulus
witnesses on the *swapped* side, namely `hUnitQ : в€Ђ k, в€ѓ q, вЂ–Ој_{k,q}вЂ– = 1`
for $Q$.  The per-block unit-modulus convention is paper-implicit in
CPSV16 В§II.C line 1182's projection argument; it is taken here as an
explicit theorem-level hypothesis (CPSV16 В§II.A line 246 records only
the global unit witness).

Paper anchor: CPSV16 В§II.C lines 1182вЂ“1186 (arXiv:1606.00608) and CPSV21
Definition 4.3 lines 1846вЂ“1884. -/
theorem forall_k_exists_j_nondecaying_overlap_of_sameMPV
    {P Q : SectorDecomposition d}
    (hP : IsBNTCanonicalForm P) (hQ : IsBNTCanonicalForm Q)
    (hUnitQ : в€Ђ k : Fin Q.basisCount, в€ѓ q : Fin (Q.copies k), вЂ–Q.weight k qвЂ– = 1)
    (hEqual : SameMPVв‚‚ P.toTensor Q.toTensor) :
    в€Ђ k : Fin Q.basisCount, в€ѓ (j : Fin P.basisCount) (h : P.basisDim j = Q.basisDim k),
      GaugePhaseEquiv
          (cast (congr_arg (MPSTensor d) h) (P.basis j))
          (Q.basis k) в€§
      В¬ Tendsto (fun N : в„• =>
          mpvOverlap (d := d) (P.basis j) (Q.basis k) N)
        atTop (рќ“ќ 0) := by
  classical
  intro k
  -- `P.basisCount > 0`: the global unit witness on `P` supplies a sector index.
  have hP_pos : 0 < P.basisCount := by
    obtain вџЁjв‚Ђ, _, _вџ© := hP.weight_unit_exists
    exact Nat.lt_of_le_of_lt (Nat.zero_le _) jв‚Ђ.isLt
  have hQ_pos : 0 < Q.basisCount := Nat.lt_of_le_of_lt (Nat.zero_le _) k.isLt
  have hEqual_symm : SameMPVв‚‚ Q.toTensor P.toTensor :=
    fun N Пѓ => (hEqual N Пѓ).symm
  obtain вџЁj, hsymDim, hGE_swapped, hNonDecay_swappedвџ© :=
    exists_block_match_of_sameMPV
      (P := Q) (Q := P) hQ hP k (hUnitQ k) hQ_pos hP_pos hEqual_symm
  refine вџЁj, hsymDim.symm, ?_, ?_вџ©
  В· exact gaugePhaseEquiv_swap_cast hsymDim.symm
      (by simpa using hGE_swapped)
  В· intro hTend
    apply hNonDecay_swapped
    exact tendsto_mpvOverlap_zero_swap (P.basis j) (Q.basis k) hTend

/-! ### Phase B-ОІ local helpers: transitivity of `GaugePhaseEquiv` at a fixed bond dim

The Phase B-ОІ bijective-matching proof composes two gauge-phase
equivalences `(P.basis j) в†” (Q.basis kв‚Ѓ)` and `(P.basis j) в†” (Q.basis kв‚‚)`
through the common centre `P.basis j` to derive an equivalence
`(Q.basis kв‚Ѓ) в†” (Q.basis kв‚‚)`.  The `basis_distinct` field of
`IsBNTCanonicalForm` then forces `kв‚Ѓ = kв‚‚` (injectivity of the matching). -/

/-- Transitivity of `GaugePhaseEquiv` at a fixed bond dimension.

If `B i = О¶в‚Ѓ вЂў (Xв‚Ѓ * A i * Xв‚ЃвЃ»В№)` and `C i = О¶в‚‚ вЂў (Xв‚‚ * B i * Xв‚‚вЃ»В№)`,
then `C i = (О¶в‚‚ О¶в‚Ѓ) вЂў ((Xв‚‚ Xв‚Ѓ) * A i * (Xв‚‚ Xв‚Ѓ)вЃ»В№)`, giving
`GaugePhaseEquiv A C` with gauge `Xв‚‚ * Xв‚Ѓ` and phase scalar `О¶в‚‚ * О¶в‚Ѓ`. -/
private theorem gaugePhaseEquiv_trans_same_dim {d D : в„•} {A B C : MPSTensor d D}
    (hв‚Ѓ : GaugePhaseEquiv A B) (hв‚‚ : GaugePhaseEquiv B C) : GaugePhaseEquiv A C := by
  classical
  obtain вџЁXв‚Ѓ, О¶в‚Ѓ, hО¶в‚Ѓ, hrв‚Ѓвџ© := hв‚Ѓ
  obtain вџЁXв‚‚, О¶в‚‚, hО¶в‚‚, hrв‚‚вџ© := hв‚‚
  refine вџЁXв‚‚ * Xв‚Ѓ, О¶в‚‚ * О¶в‚Ѓ, mul_ne_zero hО¶в‚‚ hО¶в‚Ѓ, ?_вџ©
  intro i
  -- Abbreviations for the matrix coercions of the four GL units in play.
  set Xв‚ЃM : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) в„‚ :=
    ((Xв‚Ѓ : GL (Fin D) в„‚) : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) в„‚)
  set Xв‚‚M : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) в„‚ :=
    ((Xв‚‚ : GL (Fin D) в„‚) : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) в„‚)
  set Xв‚ЃinvM : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) в„‚ :=
    ((Xв‚ЃвЃ»В№ : GL (Fin D) в„‚) : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) в„‚)
  set Xв‚‚invM : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) в„‚ :=
    ((Xв‚‚вЃ»В№ : GL (Fin D) в„‚) : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) в„‚)
  -- Coercion of the product `Xв‚‚ * Xв‚Ѓ` to a matrix is the matrix product.
  have hMul_val :
      (((Xв‚‚ * Xв‚Ѓ : GL (Fin D) в„‚)) : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) в„‚) = Xв‚‚M * Xв‚ЃM := by
    simp [Xв‚ЃM, Xв‚‚M]
  -- Coercion of the inverse of the product is the reversed product of inverses.
  have hMulInv_val :
      (((Xв‚‚ * Xв‚Ѓ)вЃ»В№ : GL (Fin D) в„‚) : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) в„‚) = Xв‚ЃinvM * Xв‚‚invM := by
    have hRev : ((Xв‚‚ * Xв‚Ѓ)вЃ»В№ : GL (Fin D) в„‚) = Xв‚ЃвЃ»В№ * Xв‚‚вЃ»В№ := mul_inv_rev Xв‚‚ Xв‚Ѓ
    have := congrArg (fun U : GL (Fin D) в„‚ =>
        (U : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) в„‚)) hRev
    simp [Xв‚ЃinvM, Xв‚‚invM]
  -- Compute `C i` by chaining the two equivalences.
  calc C i
      = О¶в‚‚ вЂў (Xв‚‚M * B i * Xв‚‚invM) := hrв‚‚ i
    _ = О¶в‚‚ вЂў (Xв‚‚M * (О¶в‚Ѓ вЂў (Xв‚ЃM * A i * Xв‚ЃinvM)) * Xв‚‚invM) := by rw [hrв‚Ѓ i]
    _ = О¶в‚‚ вЂў (О¶в‚Ѓ вЂў (Xв‚‚M * (Xв‚ЃM * A i * Xв‚ЃinvM) * Xв‚‚invM)) := by
          simp [smul_smul]
    _ = (О¶в‚‚ * О¶в‚Ѓ) вЂў (Xв‚‚M * Xв‚ЃM * A i * Xв‚ЃinvM * Xв‚‚invM) := by
          simp [smul_smul, Matrix.mul_assoc]
    _ = (О¶в‚‚ * О¶в‚Ѓ) вЂў ((Xв‚‚M * Xв‚ЃM) * A i * (Xв‚ЃinvM * Xв‚‚invM)) := by
          simp [Matrix.mul_assoc]
    _ = (О¶в‚‚ * О¶в‚Ѓ) вЂў
          ((((Xв‚‚ * Xв‚Ѓ : GL (Fin D) в„‚)) : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) в„‚) * A i *
            (((Xв‚‚ * Xв‚Ѓ)вЃ»В№ : GL (Fin D) в„‚) : Matrix (Fin D) (Fin D) в„‚)) := by
          rw [hMul_val, hMulInv_val]

/-- Composition through a common centre `A`: if the cast `D = Dв‚Ѓ` carries
`A : MPSTensor d D` into a gauge-phase equivalence with `B : MPSTensor d Dв‚Ѓ`,
and similarly the cast `D = Dв‚‚` carries `A` into a gauge-phase equivalence
with `C : MPSTensor d Dв‚‚`, then `B` and `C` are gauge-phase equivalent
(after the dimension cast `Dв‚Ѓ = Dв‚‚`).

This is the cast-aware transitivity used in Phase B-ОІ to derive
`GaugePhaseEquiv (Q.basis kв‚Ѓ) (Q.basis kв‚‚)` (up to cast) from two
matchings against the same `P.basis j`, before invoking `basis_distinct`
of `Q` to force `kв‚Ѓ = kв‚‚`. -/
private theorem gaugePhaseEquiv_cast_compose_via_centre
    {d D Dв‚Ѓ Dв‚‚ : в„•}
    (hв‚Ѓ : D = Dв‚Ѓ) (hв‚‚ : D = Dв‚‚)
    {A : MPSTensor d D} {B : MPSTensor d Dв‚Ѓ} {C : MPSTensor d Dв‚‚}
    (GEв‚Ѓ : GaugePhaseEquiv (cast (congr_arg (MPSTensor d) hв‚Ѓ) A) B)
    (GEв‚‚ : GaugePhaseEquiv (cast (congr_arg (MPSTensor d) hв‚‚) A) C) :
    GaugePhaseEquiv
        (cast (congr_arg (MPSTensor d) (hв‚Ѓ.symm.trans hв‚‚)) B) C := by
  subst hв‚Ѓ
  -- After `subst hв‚Ѓ`, `Dв‚Ѓ` is replaced everywhere by `D`, the cast on
  -- `GEв‚Ѓ` reduces to identity, and `hв‚‚.symm.trans hв‚‚ = hв‚‚`.
  subst hв‚‚
  -- After `subst hв‚‚`, all three tensors live in `MPSTensor d D`.
  simp only [cast_eq] at GEв‚Ѓ GEв‚‚ вЉў
  exact gaugePhaseEquiv_trans_same_dim (gaugePhaseEquiv_symm_same_dim GEв‚Ѓ) GEв‚‚

/-! ### Phase B-ОІ main theorem: full bijective matching by symmetry -/

/-- **CPSV16 В§II.C lines 1184вЂ“1186 full-basis bijection.**

Applying `forall_k_exists_j_nondecaying_overlap_of_sameMPV` in both
directions gives injective maps `Fin Q.basisCount в†’ Fin P.basisCount` and
`Fin P.basisCount в†’ Fin Q.basisCount`.  Finite cardinal comparison turns
the forward injection into an equivalence `ОІ : Fin Q.basisCount в‰ѓ
Fin P.basisCount`, carrying the matched bond-dimension equality,
gauge-phase equivalence, and non-decaying overlap for every sector of `Q`.

This is the Lean counterpart of the CPSV16 symmetry step "$g_A \geq g_B$
and $g_B \geq g_A$".  The proof invokes
`forall_k_exists_j_nondecaying_overlap_of_sameMPV` once with $(P,Q)$ and
once with $(Q,P)$, hence it consumes per-block unit-modulus witnesses on
both sides: `hUnitP : в€Ђ j, в€ѓ q, вЂ–Ој_{j,q}^PвЂ– = 1` and `hUnitQ : в€Ђ k, в€ѓ q,
вЂ–Ој_{k,q}^QвЂ– = 1`.  These are paper-implicit in CPSV16 В§II.C line 1182's
projection argument and are taken as explicit theorem-level hypotheses
here (CPSV16 В§II.A line 246 records only the global unit witness). -/
theorem bijective_match_of_sameMPV
    {P Q : SectorDecomposition d}
    (hP : IsBNTCanonicalForm P) (hQ : IsBNTCanonicalForm Q)
    (hUnitP : в€Ђ j : Fin P.basisCount, в€ѓ q : Fin (P.copies j), вЂ–P.weight j qвЂ– = 1)
    (hUnitQ : в€Ђ k : Fin Q.basisCount, в€ѓ q : Fin (Q.copies k), вЂ–Q.weight k qвЂ– = 1)
    (hEqual : SameMPVв‚‚ P.toTensor Q.toTensor) :
    в€ѓ ОІ : Fin Q.basisCount в‰ѓ Fin P.basisCount,
      в€Ђ k : Fin Q.basisCount, в€ѓ h : P.basisDim (ОІ k) = Q.basisDim k,
        GaugePhaseEquiv
            (cast (congr_arg (MPSTensor d) h) (P.basis (ОІ k)))
            (Q.basis k) в€§
        В¬ Tendsto (fun N : в„• =>
            mpvOverlap (d := d) (P.basis (ОІ k)) (Q.basis k) N)
          atTop (рќ“ќ 0) := by
  classical
  have hFwd :=
    forall_k_exists_j_nondecaying_overlap_of_sameMPV hP hQ hUnitQ hEqual
  have hEqual_symm : SameMPVв‚‚ Q.toTensor P.toTensor :=
    fun N Пѓ => (hEqual N Пѓ).symm
  have hBwd :=
    forall_k_exists_j_nondecaying_overlap_of_sameMPV hQ hP hUnitP hEqual_symm
  let П†в‚Ђ : Fin Q.basisCount в†’ Fin P.basisCount := fun k => (hFwd k).choose
  have П†в‚Ђ_spec : в€Ђ k : Fin Q.basisCount,
      в€ѓ h : P.basisDim (П†в‚Ђ k) = Q.basisDim k,
        GaugePhaseEquiv
            (cast (congr_arg (MPSTensor d) h) (P.basis (П†в‚Ђ k)))
            (Q.basis k) в€§
        В¬ Tendsto (fun N : в„• =>
            mpvOverlap (d := d) (P.basis (П†в‚Ђ k)) (Q.basis k) N)
          atTop (рќ“ќ 0) := fun k => (hFwd k).choose_spec
  have rebase_centre_P :
      в€Ђ (j j' : Fin P.basisCount) (_hj : j = j')
        {kv : Fin Q.basisCount}
